    <div class="page__header">
      <h1 class="page__title">Refund &amp; Cancellation Policy</h1>
      <p class="page__subtitle text-muted">Last updated: May 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-content">
      <h2>1. Cancellation Policy</h2>
      <p>You may cancel your storage unit rental at any time by providing written notice. Cancellation terms depend on your contract type:</p>

      <h3>1.1 Monthly Contracts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum 30 days' written notice is required for cancellation.</li>
        <li>A R150 administrative cancellation fee applies.</li>
        <li>No refund for the current month's payment.</li>
        <li>Pro-rata refund for any unused days in the final paid month.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.2 Quarterly (3-month) Contracts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>30 days' written notice required.</li>
        <li>No refund for the current quarter's payment.</li>
        <li>Unused future quarters are refunded in full.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.3 Bi-Annual (6-month) Contracts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>30 days' written notice required.</li>
        <li>No refund for the current period's payment.</li>
        <li>Unused future periods are refunded in full.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.4 Annual (12-month) Contracts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>30 days' written notice required.</li>
        <li>No refund for the current year's payment.</li>
        <li>Unused future months are refunded on a pro-rata basis.</li>
        <li>Discount already applied to the annual rate is retained by NSS.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How to Cancel</h2>
      <p>To cancel your booking:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Log in to your account and go to <a href="/account/bookings">My Rentals</a>.</li>
        <li>Click &ldquo;Cancel&rdquo; on the booking you wish to cancel.</li>
        <li>Or send written notice to <a href="mailto:info@nss-jbay.co.za">info@nss-jbay.co.za</a> with your booking reference.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Upon cancellation, you will receive a confirmation email. You must vacate your unit within the notice period.</p>

      <h2>3. Refund Process</h2>
      <p>Approved refunds are processed within 14 business days. Refunds are credited to the original payment method (credit card). Please allow 5-10 additional business days for the funds to appear in your account.</p>

      <h2>4. Non-Refundable Scenarios</h2>
      <p>Refunds will not be issued in the following circumstances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Early termination of an active contract without proper notice.</li>
        <li>Removal of items from the unit does not constitute cancellation.</li>
        <li>If the unit has been damaged beyond normal wear and tear.</li>
        <li>For any period during which you had access to the facility.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. No-Show Policy</h2>
      <p>If you book a unit and do not access it within 14 days of the start date without contacting us, we reserve the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact you to confirm your intentions.</li>
        <li>Release the unit to other customers after 30 days.</li>
        <li>Retain payment for the first month.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Late Payment</h2>
      <p>If payment is not received by the due date:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A reminder will be sent after 3 days.</li>
        <li>After 7 days, a late fee of R100 applies.</li>
        <li>After 14 days, access to the unit may be suspended.</li>
        <li>After 30 days, the booking is considered cancelled and the unit may be re-let.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Change of Unit Size</h2>
      <p>If you wish to change to a different unit size:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Subject to availability.</li>
        <li>Contact us and we will assist with the transfer.</li>
        <li>Price difference will be adjusted from the next billing cycle.</li>
        <li>No refund or additional charge if downgrading mid-contract (pricing adjusted from next term).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Dispute Resolution</h2>
      <p>If you disagree with a cancellation or refund decision, you may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact us at <a href="mailto:info@nss-jbay.co.za">info@nss-jbay.co.za</a> to discuss the matter.</li>
        <li>Provide additional supporting documentation.</li>
        <li>Escalate to the National Consumer Commission if necessary: <a href="https://www.compcom.co.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.compcom.co.za</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Force Majeure</h2>
      <p>In the event of circumstances beyond our control (natural disaster, facility destruction, government action), we will work with you to find a resolution, which may include temporary suspension, alternative accommodation, or full refund.</p>

